y’re one-offs. Starters are\nboilerplate projects that begin to diverge immediately from upstream\nand have no easy way of updating when changes are made\nupstream. There’s another approach to boilerplate that has become\npopular in recent years that fixes some problems with the boilerplate\napproach such as updating with upstream. One such project is\n","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1,"offset":1616},"end":{"line":40,"column":1,"offset":2002}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/"},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code>","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":2,"offset":2003},"end":{"line":40,"column":20,"offset":2021}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1,"offset":2002},"end":{"line":40,"column":67,"offset":2068}}},{"type":"text","value":". In\nthe Gatsby world, you can improve on starters similarly with themes.","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":67,"offset":2068},"end":{"line":41,"column":69,"offset":2141}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1,"offset":1616},"end":{"line":41,"column":69,"offset":2141}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"truly-reusable-themes-in-gatsby"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#truly-reusable-themes-in-gatsby","aria-label":"truly reusable themes in gatsby permalink","class":"anchor"},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg>"}]},{"type":"tex